-- MOVES-Boston Consulting strengthens capital markets practice with two hires
-- 
-- Mon Jul 14, 2014 08:39AM EDT
-- None



July 14 (Reuters) - Management consulting firm Boston Consulting Group (BCG) announced two senior appointments to its capital markets business.

The company named Charles Teschner as head of capital markets, North America, and Will Rhode as global head of capital markets research. Teschner, who will be based in New York, has 25 years of experience in the capital market industry. He joins BCG from McGraw Hill Financial Inc <MHFI.N> where he was the executive vice-president of global strategy and corporate development.